    {
      "id": "PopularPost315818",
      "post_content": "@J\\*\\*\\*Aurelius  \n  \nIt has a couple uses, though it becomes a bit of a 'build around' effect. There are a few ways to give all your enchantments hexproof or shroud ([Greater Auramancy](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Greater Auramancy),[Privileged Position](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Privileged Position), [Sterling Grove](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Sterling Grove), [Fountain Watch](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Fountain Watch)). This would allow your Kraj to take advantage of that protection without turning all of your permanents into enchantments ([Enchanted Evening](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Enchanted Evening)). It protects him from all direct damage and creature destruction/exiling effects at the expense of making him vulnerable to enchantment destruction. Hard to say whether or not the trade-off is worth it, but in the right deck, perhaps.",
      "posted_by": "Keldane",
      "html": "<div class=\"post evenItem\" id=\"PopularPost315818\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl04_post\">@J***Aurelius<br/><br/>It has a couple uses, though it becomes a bit of a 'build around' effect. There are a few ways to give all your enchantments hexproof or shroud (<a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Greater Auramancy\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Greater Auramancy\">Greater Auramancy</a>,<a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Privileged Position\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Privileged Position\">Privileged Position</a>, <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Sterling Grove\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Sterling Grove\">Sterling Grove</a>, <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Fountain Watch\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Fountain Watch\">Fountain Watch</a>). This would allow your Kraj to take advantage of that protection without turning all of your permanents into enchantments (<a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Enchanted Evening\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Enchanted Evening\">Enchanted Evening</a>). It protects him from all direct damage and creature destruction/exiling effects at the expense of making him vulnerable to enchantment destruction. Hard to say whether or not the trade-off is worth it, but in the right deck, perhaps.</span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl04_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"../../Classes/Controls/#\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl04_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '315818'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                    \r\n                            </div>